  "text": "Given that state-TPs can be effectively primed [CITATION_1] , we also expect that transient focus on a particular time horizon should influence situational motivation, and, indirectly, enhance or diminish sport performance. Directing athletes' attention to more distant goals and particular steps leading to realization of these goals could strengthen momentary motivation, allowing them to restrain from letting go of the training scheduled for a given day (cf. [CITATION_2] , whereas reflection on positive moments from one's past sport career could foster situational levels of their sense of competence, indirectly supporting IM.",
